Defendant Juan D Robles in court with attorney Heather L. Johnson.  Defendant Juan D Robles in custody.  Joshua M. Mathy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Clerk;ds

Martha Hernandez, intepreter, sworn-in.  Defense moves to adjourn the sentencing.  Court denies motion.  Sentencing proceeds. State has complied with victim notification.  Statements by counsel and defendant. COURT ADVISES the defendant he cannot possess firearms or body armor, he must provide a DNA sample if not previously provided and pay the DNA surcharge and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  

COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE - 30 years with 186 days credit -  INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT - 20 years  -  EXTENDED SUPERVISION - 10 years; pay costs, assessments and surcharges by the end of the sentence or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant and subject to other collection.  

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  1) no violations of criminal law rising to the level of probable cause; 2) pay any monetary amounts ordered but not paid while in the institution; 3) sex offender treatment; 4) mental health evaluation; 5) no contact with Pilar R or AF DOB: 7-20-01.

Court finds defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.

COURT ORDERS:
-  defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis and pay the surcharge - if not already done
-  DOC to collect those monetary sums/amounts at the rate of 25% of funds;
- defendant to have no contact with Pilar R. or AF DOB: 7-20-01 during the entire length of the sentence.    Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping;
- defendant to comply with sex offender reporting requirements;
- defendant cannot work or volunteer with children under the age of 16;
- restitution set at -0-.

Appeal rights given.  Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence and Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief and Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgment received and filed.  Copies given to the defendant.
